frameDefinitions: This is an abstract frame for durative activities, in which the Agent enters an ongoing state of the Activity, remains in this state for some Duration of Time, and leaves this state either by finishing or by stopping.
This frame contains words that describe a set of individuals which possess some Commonality, generally a common attribute.
This frame describes a situation in which an Owner loses his or her Possession.
A Person or Institution is being described in terms of their wealthiness, in other words the amount of money in their possession.
This frame has to do with nouns denoting types of entities.
frameExamples: I don't like this newfangled <t><fex name='Subtype'>kind</fex></t> of  fish.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Activity</fen> occurs.

This role denotes the people in possession of the Commonality. This role is usually genetive, the object of a postnominal PP, or null instantiated (INI), and null instantiaton often implies the public at large, as in 'the common good'.
This role denotes an object or attribute which is jointly posessed by the <fen>Entities</fen>.
One of the possesors of the <fen>Commonality</fen>. Can be singular or plural.
One of the possesors of the <fen>Commonality</fen>. Can be singular or plural.
The object that is possessed by the <fen>Owner</fen>.
The individual or individuals whose wealthiness is being described.
A group which has (or lacks) possession of some resource.
The entity which denotes a subtype of the more general <fen>Category</fen>.
The more general type that the target denotes a subtype of. This role is obligatory and should be labeled DNI when not present.
listRoleExamples: Their shared <fex>parents</fex> were their only similarity.
<fex>Pat and Kim</fex> are completely broke at the moment.
I don't like this <fex>kind</fex> of fish.
They created a new breed <fex>of dog</fex>.
